The paper deals with algorithms for the shortest $k$-disjoint path problem on planar graphs, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The techniques used involve determinants and cycle covers, which are common tools in computational geometry and algebraic combinatorics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CG (computational geometry), and cs.DM (discrete mathematics). Additionally, the paper involves randomized and deterministic algorithms, which are relevant to cs.CC (computational complexity) and cs.NA (numerical analysis).
